The prenatal diagnosis and early endoscopic section of ureterocele. The endoscopic incision of ureterocele in children is still a controversial procedure. In two Departments of Pediatric Surgery, between January 1990 and December 1994, 47 patients (34 females, 13 males), for a total of 53 ureteroceles, underwent endoscopic incision of the ureterocele as the primary form of treatment 41 ureteroceles were in duplex kidney. In 33 cases (70%) the prenatal ultrasound had observed hydronephrosis or duplex kidney or the presence of the ureterocele